Said I would not come into restaurant for a drink and asked for general manager to return call.  He never did! Four messages later, no return call.  Final call #5, this manager insisted he could resolve problem because “Joe” usually not there and at other Bethesda store. He offered same compensation The first person did, then backtracked on the entree. Had enough of the unprofessional treatment and malingering on the phone and no return calls from manager, so took the empanadas back and requested a refund which was refused. When I returned the empanadas, they took them into the restaurant were gone for several minutes came back with them and refused refund. They left again for several minutes  still with item and no intention to refund. After having two employees harass me, one whom approached the driver’s window I left. They still have the empanadas.  Take out order no napkins or silverware, cold empanadas that look nothing like the picture on their web page with no seasoning or the sauce requested, multiple calls and messages left for the manager that were ignored, refused reimbursement, harassment to the point one approached the driver window. At that point, felt threatened and left.  They made no effort to address the problem, no apologies, no refund. Rather held me hostage For 15 minutes awaiting a refund they had no intention of giving and then they had nothing better to do than harass me for a receipt.  When this guy approached my car again, I couldn’t take the harassment anymore until I just left.  They are unwilling to acknowledge any problems with their food or service with carry out!!!!  When I handed it to them I said “ They were cold, there was no seasoning or sauce as requested.”  That answer wasn’t sufficient for them. Will file a formal complaint with the county! BEWARE BEWARE BEWARE OF CARRY OUT WITH THEM!

Please train your servers to do a 2-3 minute check back after dropping food to the table to ensure your guests are satisfied and have everything that they need to enjoy their meal. I am a server an excellent one by the way and a $60 meal which is normally a $10-$15 tip ended up being a 10% tip and I have never in my life tipped that low. I just won’t be back I wish I could but it was not a good experience and my husband was very disappointed that I had chose that restaurant only bc of the poor conditions. He loved the food too. Please update the restaurant and get it up to a healthy and more presentable standard. Code enforcement should really evaluate the mold and all the moisture growing in the ceiling. Especially charging $20 plus for most dishes and $16 for a Cuban sandwich!? Outrageous! Good luck! We won’t be back unfortunately. My favorite dish is Masitas de Puerco Cuba Libre, deliciously savory pork morsels,  fried to create a tender, crisp outer layer with juicy, succulent pork inside. I loved Cubanos, until April 19th!!!  I was between appointments and starving, placed my order and explained I had a limited amount of time. Then the unforgettable downfall followed.  They served me leftovers, refried so hard they sounded like dominoes on my plate, dressed up with onion slices that must have counted one slice for each piece of pork.  The Black Bean Soup was tepid, barely warmed, I pointed things out to the waiter. After my complaint the waiter returned with a sincere apology from the chef who admitted to the reheated old food and serving twice fried, overcooked leftovers. Then i was given a check for the full amount.  Soooooo disappointing. On the bright side that nasty experience will help me to actively avoid Cubanos, I really was in no mood to argue, I was charged full price and paid it. Reluctantly.  Poor quality presentations, badly cooked dishes, re-serving leftovers then the failure to show some integrity and comp the full meal will make it easy for me to remember delicious meals at Cubanos as a distant past that may not return. I'll keep my money in my pocket and sail right past.
